{
    "id": "uniobjectutil",
    "lang": "en-us",
    "name": "UniObjectUtil",
    "description": "The most-used library: move, rotate, scale, show/hide, spawn, and destroy objects — and find other objects and scripts in your scene.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/uniobjectutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "uniobjectutil",
        "transform",
        "position",
        "spawn",
        "scene"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "Utility",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/utility"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "VectorUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/vectorutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "UniObjectUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "This is the library you'll reach for most often. Everything in your scene — a cube, a coin, a player, a camera — is an **object**. `UniObjectUtil` lets you move, rotate, scale, show, hide, spawn, and destroy those objects, and find other objects and their scripts."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "note",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Most methods take `uniscript` as the first parameter, meaning **which object**. Pass `this` to act on the object your script is attached to."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Moving, rotating, and scaling"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "An object's **transform** is its position (where it is), rotation (which way it faces), and scale (how big it is). These methods read and change all three:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`SetPosition(this, pos)` / `GetPosition(this)`", "Set or read the object's position (a `vector3`)."],
                ["`SetScale(this, scale)` / `GetScale(this)`", "Set or read the object's size."],
                ["`SetRotation(this, rot)` / `GetRotation(this)`", "Set or read the object's rotation (a `quaternion`)."],
                ["`Translate(this, x, y, z)`", "Nudge the object by an amount, **relative to the way it faces** (forward, up, right)."],
                ["`Rotate(this, x, y, z)`", "Spin the object by these degrees on each axis."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Place the object at a specific spot.",
                "UniObjectUtil.SetPosition(this, VectorUtil.New(0.0, 5.0, 0.0));",
                "",
                "// Slowly spin it every frame.",
                "UniObjectUtil.Rotate(this, 0.0, 90.0 * Time.DeltaTime(), 0.0);",
                "",
                "// Push it forward (the direction it's facing).",
                "UniObjectUtil.Translate(this, 0.0, 0.0, 2.0 * Time.DeltaTime());"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "h3",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Local vs. world position"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "When an object sits *inside* another object (a wheel on a car), it has two positions: its **local** position (relative to its parent) and its **world** position (its true spot in the scene)."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "Use when"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`SetPosition` / `GetPosition`", "You want the position **relative to the parent** (local)."],
                ["`SetWorldPosition` / `GetWorldPosition`", "You want the true position **in the world**."],
                ["`SetWorldRotation` / `GetWorldRotation`", "The true facing in the world (uses a `vector3` of angles)."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "note",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "If an object has no parent, its local and world positions are the same, so either pair works."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "warning",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "**Moving a camera?** Use `SetPosition` — `SetWorldPosition` silently does nothing on a camera object. See [CameraUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/camerautil) for camera-specific guidance."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Facing a direction (aiming)"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "To make an object point toward something, build a rotation with [QuaternionUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/quaternionutil)'s `LookRotation` and apply it with `SetRotation`. `LookRotation` needs a direction to look along plus an \"up\" direction:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Aim this object at a target's position.",
                "vector3 myPos     = UniObjectUtil.GetWorldPosition(this);",
                "vector3 targetPos = UniObjectUtil.GetWorldPosition(target);",
                "vector3 direction = VectorUtil.Normalized(targetPos - myPos);",
                "",
                "quaternion look = QuaternionUtil.LookRotation(direction, VectorUtil.Up());",
                "UniObjectUtil.SetRotation(this, look);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "You can also read an object's own direction vectors — handy for shooting forward or strafing sideways:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-017",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "Returns"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Forward(this)`", "The direction the object is facing."],
                ["`Right(this)`", "The direction to its right."],
                ["`Up(this)`", "The direction above it."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-018",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Showing, hiding, and removing"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-019",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`SetUniObjectActivation(this, true/false)`", "Turns the object on (visible & active) or off (hidden & inactive)."],
                ["`GetUniObjectActivation(this)`", "`true` if the object is currently active."],
                ["`Destroy(this)`", "Permanently removes the object from the scene."],
                ["`GetName(this)` / `SetName(this, name)`", "Read or change the object's name."],
                ["`GetNumberOfComponents(this)`", "How many components the object has."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-020",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Temporarily hide a door, then show it again later.",
                "UniObjectUtil.SetUniObjectActivation(doorScript, false);  // hide",
                "UniObjectUtil.SetUniObjectActivation(doorScript, true);   // show",
                "",
                "// Remove a collected coin.",
                "UniObjectUtil.Destroy(this);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-021",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Hiding an object with `SetUniObjectActivation(..., false)` keeps it in the scene so you can show it again. Use `Destroy` only when the object is gone for good."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-022",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Spawning new objects"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-023",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "**Spawning** (instantiating) creates a fresh copy of a saved object — a bullet, a coin, an enemy — while the game is running. You wire the object to copy into an asset field, then spawn it by name."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-024",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Instantiate(asset, name)`", "Spawns a copy of `asset`, giving the new object the chosen `name`."],
                ["`InstantiateAndCallback(asset, name, script, method, data)`", "Spawns, then calls `method` on `script` once the new object is ready — so you can position it, set its speed, etc."],
                ["`New(name)`", "Creates a brand-new empty object with the given name."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-025",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "class Spawner",
                "{",
                "    UniAsset @bulletAsset;",
                "",
                "    void Fire()",
                "    {",
                "        // Spawn a bullet, then set it up in OnBulletReady.",
                "        UniObjectUtil.InstantiateAndCallback(bulletAsset, \"Bullet\", this, \"OnBulletReady\", null);",
                "    }",
                "",
                "    void OnBulletReady(object newBullet)",
                "    {",
                "        // Position and aim the new bullet here.",
                "    }",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-026",
            "tag": "important",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`Instantiate` runs in the background, so the new object isn't ready on the very next line. When you need to set up the spawned object immediately, use `InstantiateAndCallback` — its callback fires exactly when the object is ready."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-027",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Parents and children"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-028",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Objects can be nested. A child object moves with its parent — perfect for attaching things together."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-029",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`SetParent(this, parent)`", "Makes this object a child of `parent`."],
                ["`GetParent(this)`", "Returns this object's parent."],
                ["`GetChilds(this)`", "Returns a list of this object's direct children."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-030",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Finding other objects and scripts"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-031",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "To make objects talk to each other, you first need a reference to the other object's script. These methods find them."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-032",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it finds"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`FindUniObjectsByTag(tag)`", "A list of every object in the scene with that tag — the fastest way to find groups (all coins, all enemies)."],
                ["`GetUniObject(this)`", "The object that owns this script (a handle you can pass around)."],
                ["`GetScriptByName(this, name)`", "A script with that name on this same object."],
                ["`GetScriptByIndex(this, index)`", "A script by its position in the object's component list."],
                ["`GetScriptInChildren(this, name)` / `GetScriptInParents(this, name)`", "The first matching script among this object's children / parents."],
                ["`GetScriptsByName` / `GetScriptsInChildren` / `GetScriptsInParents`", "Like above, but return a **list** of all matches."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-033",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Tag your coins \"coin\" in the editor, then find them all.",
                "List coins = UniObjectUtil.FindUniObjectsByTag(\"coin\");",
                "Debug.Log(\"There are \" + ListUtil.Count(coins) + \" coins left.\");"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-034",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Searching by **tag** is fast and reliable. Give related objects the same tag in the editor, then grab them all with `FindUniObjectsByTag`. See [ListUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/listutil) for working with the list you get back."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-035",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Scripts and extras on an object"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-036",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`AttachScript(this, name)`", "Adds a script (by class name) to the object while the game runs."],
                ["`DetachScript(this)`", "Removes the script. Returns `false` if other components still need it."],
                ["`GetScriptActivation(this)` / `SetScriptActivation(this, on)`", "Turn a single script on or off without removing it."],
                ["`Add3DText(this)`", "Adds floating 3D text to the object."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-037",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-038",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`bool`", "`Instantiate`", "`object asset, string name`"],
                ["`bool`", "`InstantiateAndCallback`", "`object asset, string name, uniscript, string callbackMethod, object refData`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetPosition`", "`uniscript, vector3 position`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`GetPosition`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetRotation`", "`uniscript, quaternion rotation`"],
                ["`quaternion`", "`GetRotation`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetScale`", "`uniscript, vector3 scale`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`GetScale`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`bool`", "`GetUniObjectActivation`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetUniObjectActivation`", "`uniscript, bool enabled`"],
                ["`int`", "`GetNumberOfComponents`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`Destroy`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`string`", "`GetName`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetName`", "`uniscript, string name`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetActivation`", "`uniscript, bool enabled`"],
                ["`void`", "`Translate`", "`uniscript, float x, float y, float z`"],
                ["`uniscript`", "`GetUniObject`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`uniscript`", "`AttachScript`", "`uniscript, string name`"],
                ["`bool`", "`DetachScript`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`uniscript`", "`GetScriptByIndex`", "`uniscript, int index`"],
                ["`uniscript`", "`GetScriptByName`", "`uniscript, string name`"],
                ["`bool`", "`GetScriptActivation`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetScriptActivation`", "`uniscript, bool enabled`"],
                ["`void`", "`Rotate`", "`uniscript, float x, float y, float z`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`GetWorldPosition`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetWorldPosition`", "`uniscript, vector3 position`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Forward`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Right`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`Up`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetParent`", "`uniscript, uniscript`"],
                ["`List`", "`GetChilds`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`Add3DText`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`uniscript`", "`GetParent`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`vector3`", "`GetWorldRotation`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetWorldRotation`", "`uniscript, vector3 position`"],
                ["`uniscript`", "`New`", "`string name`"],
                ["`uniscript`", "`GetScriptInChildren`", "`uniscript, string name`"],
                ["`uniscript`", "`GetScriptInParents`", "`uniscript, string name`"],
                ["`List`", "`GetScriptsByName`", "`uniscript, string name`"],
                ["`List`", "`GetScriptsInChildren`", "`uniscript, string name`"],
                ["`List`", "`GetScriptsInParents`", "`uniscript, string name`"],
                ["`List`", "`FindUniObjectsByTag`", "`string tag`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-039",
            "tag": "warning",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "To make an object **face** a target, use `SetRotation` together with `QuaternionUtil.LookRotation` (shown in [Facing a direction](/docs/uniscript/en-us/uniobjectutil#block-013)). The `LookAt` style helpers are not currently available from UniScript."
        }
    ]
}
